article.headline: Orth, Minter lead South Alabama in 45-7 rout of Alabama St.
article.description: Evan Orth and Tra Minter accounted for two touchdowns apiece to lead South Alabama in a 45-7 rout of Alabama State on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Orth, Minter lead South Alabama in 45-7 rout of Alabama St.

images.name: Jaguars break off 75-yard punt return for TD
images.caption: RB Tra Minter receives the punt and shows off his speed, blazing past tacklers and taking it all the way to the house to make it 35-7 South Alabama.

video.headline: Jaguars break off 75-yard punt return for TD
video.caption: RB Tra Minter receives the punt and shows off his speed, blazing past tacklers and taking it all the way to the house to make it 35-7 South Alabama.
video.title: Jaguars break off 75-yard punt return for TD
video.description: RB Tra Minter receives the punt and shows off his speed, blazing past tacklers and taking it all the way to the house to make it 35-7 South Alabama.

article.story: MOBILE, Ala. -- Evan Orth and Tra Minter accounted for two touchdowns apiece to lead South Alabama in a 45-7 rout of Alabama State on Saturday night. South Alabama (2-5) played its first home game in nearly a month and snapped a three-game losing streak. Orth was 12 of 15 for 155 yards passing and threw a nine-yard score to Jordan McCray. Orth added 31 yards rushing and a 19-yard TD run. Tra Minter had an eight-yard touchdown run in the first quarter, and later ran untouched 75 yards into the end zone on a punt return to make it 35-7 early in the fourth. Kawaan Baker also had a touchdown run, and Jahmmir Taylor caught a 56-yard touchdown pass from Cephus Johnson for the Jaguars. KHA'Darris Davis connected with Tyrek Allen on a 75-yard touchdown pass to pull Alabama State (2-4) to 14-7 midway through the second quarter.

videos.headline: South Alabama strikes first with 8-yard TD run
videos.description: RB Tra Minter somehow stays on his feet and gets himself across the goal line, giving the Jaguars an early 7-0 lead.

videos.headline: South Alabama doubles lead on 3-yard jet sweep
videos.description: WR Kawaan Baker takes the hand off and gets the edge, scoring easily to make it 14-0 Jaguars.

videos.headline: Alabama State explodes for 75-yard TD pass
videos.description: QB KHA'Darris Davis unloads a pass to WR Tyrek Allen, who brings it down and outruns the defense, cutting the Jaguars' lead to 14-7.

videos.headline: South Alabama responds with 20-yard QB run
videos.description: QB Evan Orth keeps it himself and slips through tackles en route to the end zone, extending the Jaguars' lead to 21-7.

videos.headline: Jaguars widen lead with 14-yard TD pass
videos.description: QB Evan Orth throws a dime to WR Jordan McCray, who makes a leaping reception in the end zone to make it 28-7 South Alabama.

videos.headline: South Alabama pours it on with 56-yard TD pass
videos.description: Backup QB Cephus Johnson puts one on the money to WR Jahmmir Taylor, who gets to the end zone and makes it 45-7 Jaguars.
